text: Debt is a liability that must be paid off

If I own a home worth $5 million - it is an irrelevant figure unless we adjust for the size of the home mortgage (if it exists)… for goodness sake. @RiskReversal If I owe $2 million (home loan) my equity is only $3 million and not $5 million (if owned loan free).

When will people understand that $AAPL cash on the balance sheet (about $250 billion) is not a relevant figure? The company has over $100 billion of debt. So net cash is under $150 billion - the lowest level since late 2014. @RiskReversal
